he Queenside.} 17. Nxc4 b5 {Forcing a favorable trade, which enables us to activate our Rook and reduce White's activity to a minimum.} 18. cxb6 axb6 19. Qb4 Nd5 20. Nxd5 Bxd5 ({Our control over the d5 -square, coupled with the bishop pair and active Rook, gives us full compensation for the sacrificed pawn. Note that Nxb6 drops a piece to} 20... Rb8 {.}) *

