b5 axb5 16. axb5 Bb7 {Calmly protecting the c6 -pawn while completing our development.} 17. bxc6 Bxc6 18. Ra6 Qd7 {Once again, calmly deflecting the threat and connecting our Rooks.} 19. Be3 Ne6 {Completing the optimization of the knight, which now exerts long-term pressure against White's center and can also be used to smoke the Rook out of a6 .} 20. Nf4 Nc7 21. Ra2 Nb5 {The bishop pair, coupled with the outside passed pawn on a7 , gives us excellent chances. Note that the protected passer on c5 is entirely immobilized by our light-square control.} *

