1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. c4 Nb6 4. a4 {A rare system that is not particularly promising. The inclusion of a4 and ... a5 will favor Black, since we will secure a nice outpost on b4 .} a5 5. Ra3 {A cute-looking move, but neglecting the development leads to unpleasant consequences if Black responds accurately.} e6 {A nonstandard response (usually we open the center by pushing our d-pawn), but the compromised position of White's Rook demands a slightly different approach.} 6. Rg3 Nc6 {Developing and hitting e5 .} 7. Nc3 d6 {The pawn on e5 is poisoned due to the cute tactic c4 - c5 , when Black cannot recapture due to the fork. For this reason, we liquidate the e5 -pawn without capturing it.} 8. exd6 Bxd6 {Sacrificing the g7 -pawn for the sake of development.} 9. Rxg7 e5 {An important multi-purpose move, reinforcing our control over the d4 -square and opening the diagonal for our light-squared bishop.} 10. Bd3 h5 {Garnering the g4 -square for the bishop and stopping Qh5 .} 11. Nf3 Bg4 {With the lovely hidden threat of ... Bf8 , setting up a double attack against the Rook and the bishop!} 12. Rh7 {White has no choice but to liquidate his only strong piece.} Rxh7 13. Bxh7 Nd4 {We are down a pawn, but are dominating White in terms of development and control over key squares. Furthermore, White has no safe post for their king.} 14. Be4 f5 15. Bxb7 e4 {Complete domination! White has to find nearly-impossible only moves, one after the other, to stay afloat. In practical terms, the position is virtually hopeless.} 16. h3 Nxf3+ 17. gxf3 Bxf3 18. Qb3 Bxh1 19. Qb5+ Ke7 {Avoiding all of the nasty checks.} 20. Bxa8 Qg8 {Activity over everything - delivering checkmate is a bit more important than taking the bishop, which would fail to c4 - c5 .} 21. c5 {Another only move, preparing to cover the check with the queen.} Qg1+ 22. Qf1 Qxf1+ 23. Kxf1 Bxc5 {The smoke has finally cleared. Material is equal, but look at White's pawns! The position is equal according to the engine, but White must continue to work hard in order to keep the balance.} *

